# Supabase Configuration for CSR (Client-Side Rendering)
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key_here

# 🔧 FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file: cp env.example .env
# 2. Fill in your actual Supabase values
# 3. Run: npm run dev

# ⚠️  IMPORTANT FOR NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT:
# You MUST set these environment variables in Netlify:
# 1. Go to Netlify Dashboard
# 2. Select your site
# 3. Go to Site Settings > Environment Variables
# 4. Add these variables with your actual Supabase values:
#    - Key: VITE_SUPABASE_URL, Value: https://your-actual-project-id.supabase.co
#    - Key: VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, Value: your_actual_anon_key
# 5. Redeploy your site

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to your Supabase project dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Settings > API
# 3. Copy the Project URL to VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# 4. Copy the anon/public key to VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 5. Save this file as .env in your project root
#
# Note: For CSR, we only need the anon key as we're not using server-side operations

# IMPORTANT: For Netlify deployment, you MUST set these as environment variables in:
# Netlify Dashboard > Site Settings > Environment Variables